etymology.description: Phonetic 丯 (jiè, no direct meaning) + Semantic 刀(刀) (dāo, "knife") = to engrave
etymology.interpretation: The character 㓞(㓞) (jiè, "carve, engrave") combines the phonetic element 丯 (jiè) with the semantic 刀(刀) (dāo, "knife") to suggest an action involving cutting or carving. 刀(刀) (dāo) clearly indicates a tool used for engraving, while 丯 serves as the phonetic guide.
